    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-18T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/932: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-18T21:00:00+03:00"
                            >January 18, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 19—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. I transmitted to Molotov<note n="69" xml:id="d755fn69">Vyacheslav
                        Mikailovich Molotov, People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the Soviet
                        Union.</note> on January 17 the information contained in the Department’s
                    85, January 14, 11 p.m., and requested an urgent reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
